        <div class="faq">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3 onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I delete my Blooger account?</h3>
                <div class="faq-content">
                    <p>You can delete your account at any time:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Go to your Account Settings</li>
                        <li>Select "Account Management"</li>
                        <li>Choose "Delete Account"</li>
                        <li>Confirm your decision</li>
                    </ol>
                    <p>Account deletion is permanent and removes all your content. Contact support if you need assistance.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3 onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I control who sees my posts?</h3>
                <div class="faq-content">
                    <p>Yes, Blooger offers several privacy options:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Public:</strong> Visible to anyone, including search engines</li>
                        <li><strong>Followers Only:</strong> Visible to your approved followers</li>
                        <li><strong>Private:</strong> Only visible to you</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>You can adjust these settings when creating or editing any post. You can also change default privacy settings in your account preferences.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3 onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How does Blooger use cookies?</h3>
                <div class="faq-content">
                    <p>We use cookies to enhance your experience:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> To keep you logged in during your session</li>
                        <li><strong>Preferences:</strong> To remember your language, theme, and other settings</li>
                        <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> To understand how users interact with our platform</li>
                        <li><strong>Security:</strong> To detect and prevent fraudulent activity</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>You can manage cookie preferences in your browser settings. Note that disabling cookies may affect some Blooger features.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3 onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How can I report inappropriate content?</h3>
                <div class="faq-content">
                    <p>If you encounter content that violates our guidelines:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Click the "•••" menu on the post</li>
                        <li>Select "Report Content"</li>
                        <li>Choose the reason for reporting</li>
                        <li>Add any additional context</li>
                        <li>Submit your report</li>
